sentences: Anđelka Bego-Šimunić (born 23 October 1941) is a Bosnian-Herzegovinian composer of Croatian descent.
She studied composition at the academy under Ivan Brkanović and Miroslav Špiler, earning a master's degree in 1973.
She joined the staff of the academy in 1975, and later became assistant (1985) and full professor at the academy, where her students include Igor Karaca.
